         DNP Waters business model mainly consists of the development and acquisition of water treatment projects and water supply companies. While DNP Waters ownership varies from project to project, it usually seeks a majority shareholding in operations whether greenfield or brownfield projects.  


         DNP Waters existing water treatment and supply operations (directly and indirectly owned) include: i) 71% ownership of the Binh Hiep water company; ii) 53% ownership of the Dong Tam water plant; iii) 26% ownership stake in the Long An water company; iv) 30% ownership of the Nhi Thanh water project; and v) 33% ownership of the Bac Giang water project. The companys activities cover 240,000 m3/day of treatment and / or supply capacity. 


         The International Finance Corporation (IFC)  the private sector investment arm of the World Bank Group  is considering a convertible loan investment in DNP Water to support its growth in the Vietnam water sector.

